OL,3,CNew right to ask for flexible working
OL,4,Cfrom first day in job comes into force
OL,6,FJoeli Brearley, chief executive of the
OL,7,Fgroup, said: "Mothers are more likely
OL,8,Fto shoulder the lion's share of the
OL,9,Funpaid labour required to care for
OL,10,Fchildren and manage a household.
OL,12,F"As a result, they are more likely to
OL,13,Fneed flexible working. Just three in
OL,14,F10 job adverts offer flexibility,
OL,15,Flimiting the progression opportunities
OL,16,Fand earning potential of mothers.
OL,18,F"Then we wonder why the gender pay gap
OL,19,Fwidens when couples have children and
OL,20,Fcontinues to widen further over the
OL,21,Fsubsequent decades."
